etymologies: early 17th century: from Latin quintilis (mensis) ‘fifth month, July’, from quintus ‘fifth’

definitions: any of five equal groups into which a population can be divided according to the distribution of values of a particular variable.
shortDefinitions: any of five equal groups into which population can be divided according to distribution of values of particular variable

definitions: each of the four values of the random variable that divide a population into five groups.
shortDefinitions: each of four values of random variable which divide population into quintiles

definitions: an aspect of 72° (one fifth of a circle).
